                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works. Occasionally, the word God is rubricated in alternating red and black letters (e.g., <locus target="#7v"/>).</desc>
                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#129v #130r"/> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#141r 141v"/> (tenth Biblical Canticle).</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iiv(erso)"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1066DavidHarp"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#12r"/><desc> The Ancient of Days, surrounded by <ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1096SavioroftheWorld"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#12v"/><desc> The Ancient of Days, surrounded by <ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1096SavioroftheWorld"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#18r"/><desc> A <ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1035HolyMan"/> being led away by evil people (showing one eye), <persName ref="PRS5684JesusCh"/> in the garden(?)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#18v"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1005Crucifixion"/>, with <persName ref="PRS5684JesusCh"/> surrounded by soldiers with <term key="spear"/> and <term key="shield"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#37r"/><desc>Two animals grazing under a fruit tree, one larger than the other with caption <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ኃየል፡ ምስለ፡ ወልድ፡</foreign>, “A powerful [beast] with a son.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#106v"/><desc>upper margin: an ornate flower</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#109v"/><desc>interlocking circles</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#110r"/><desc> Ornate <ref type ="authFile" corresp="AT1071Cross"/>(?) with a bird (dove?) descending</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type = "frame" xml:id="d10">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #8r #17r #26v #46r #52r #61r #73v #82rv #88v #102r #114v #117v #124r #132r #145v"/> (haräg);
                    <locus target="#7v #154r #157r #159r #160r #162r"/> (small cross);
                    <locus target="#145r"/> (line of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#156v"/> (line of black dots).
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso)"/>, first two lines: Lucky and Unlucky Days of the Year <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጽንዕት፡ ወጽንጽንት፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    <locus target="#iv(erso) #ii r(ecto)"/>: Asmat prayer against wild animals, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ መስተሃድር፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto) #167r"/>, in pencil: List of the feast days of the Apostles and Evangelists
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#130v #131r #131v #69v #70r #70v"/>: <title type="incomplete" ref="LIT3085RepCh365"/>, incomplete at the end
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#167v"/>, upper: Spiritual Rewards (fruits) for reciting the Lord’s Prayer and the Hail, Mary, written in blue ink, in a crude hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#46r #166v"/>: the name of the owner is Wäldä Maryam
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a7">
                    <desc type="ScribalSignature">
                    <locus target="#70v"/>: mentions the scribe, Za-Mäsqäl, and the owner, Kasaye
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#67r"/>: the mid-point of the Psalms is marked with the words “Half of David.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#166v"/>: illegible note, in pencil
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#167v"/>, lower: pen trial
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    It is unclear what manuscript this is in the insurance hand list
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                    Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#6r #25v #27r #29v #32r"/>, etc.); and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#13v #23v"/>); and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#103v"/>, line 20); text has been removed (<locus target="#56r #84r #85v #86v #88r"/>, etc.).
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    </list>
